      details:"Prior to beginning the Gokyo Valley Circuit Trek with Gokyo Lakes, there is time to rest and acclimatize at Namche. The Khumbu region includes the bustling town of Namche Bazaar. There are a lot of conveniences, such as bakeries, restaurants, ATMs, and Internet caf√©s. Before embarking on a tour of the neighborhood, you could briefly stop at a viewpoint like Thame or Khunde. To find out more about Sherpa culture, Everest climbers, and their rituals, go to the Tourist Visitor Center. The Everest View Hotel is also reachable via hiking. From here, one can see a wide range of mountains, including Everest, Ama Dablam, Lhotse, Nuptse, Cho-Oyu, Thamserku, and many others. You will see the area for a while before returning to Namche for the evening.",
